E PROPORTION OF READERS IN THE ELDERLY POPULATION OF QUEBEC AND OF CANADA.     PRESENTS STATISTICAL DATA COMPARING QUEBEC WITH CANADA AS A WHOLE, ON THEPROPORTION OF READERS IN THE ADULT POPULATION; AND ON THE PROPORTION OFREADERS OF VARIOUS TYPES OF MATERIAL IN THE ELDERLY (OVER 65) POPULATION. THEPOSITION OF THE ELDERLY POPULATION IS THEN COMPARED WITH THAT OF THE TOTALADULT POPULATION, AND IN CONCLUSION DISCUSSES THE PROBABILITY THAT THE NUMBEROF ELDERLY READERS, AND PUBLIC LIBRARY USERS, WILL INCREASE, NECESSITATINGEXPANSION OF LIBRARY FACILITIES TO MEET THEIR DEMANDS